{{Infobox person |image=Charles E. Goad - Christmas 1879.jpg |birth_place=Camberwell, [[Surrey, England]] |birth_date=March 15, 1848 |death_place=[[Toronto|Toronto, Ontario]], Canada |death_date={{dda|1910|6|10|1848|3|15}} |occupation=[[cartographer]] and [[civil engineer]] |nationality= }} '''Charles Edward Goad''' (March 15, 1848 – June 10, 1910 ) was a noted [[cartographer]] and [[civil engineer]]. Goad is most noted for his insurance surveys of cities in Canada, Great Britain, and elsewhere. Fire insurance companies needed to know in detail the nature and size of buildings, width of streets, construction, building materials and the proximity of fire services and water supplies in order to estimate appropriate premiums. Goad established a company (the ''Charles E. Goad Company'') in 1875 in Montreal, Quebec, Canada to produce maps to provide this information. These and like maps are now referred to as [[Goad maps]]. Goad returned to England in 1885 and began work in Britain.<ref> Rowley,Gwyn (2004) 'Goad, Charles Edward (1848–1910)', Oxford Dictionary of National Biography</ref><ref>[http://www.mcrh.mmu.ac.uk/pubs/pdf/mrhr_03ii_rowley.pdf Rowley, Gwyn (1984) Fire insurance plans] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110930144424/http://www.mcrh.mmu.ac.uk/pubs/pdf/mrhr_03ii_rowley.pdf |date=2011-09-30 }}, Charles E. Goad Ltd</ref><ref>Rowley, Gwyn (1994) 'Fire Insurance Plans', in Helen Wallis (ed.), Historians' Guide to Early British Maps</ref>
Goad was a member of the following societies: * [[American Society of Civil Engineers]] * [[Canadian Society of Civil Engineers]] * [[London Chamber of Commerce & Industry]] * Engineers' Club of New York * [[Statistical Society of London]] * [[Imperial Institute]]
The Goad trademark is now a part of [[Experian]].<ref>[http://www.experian.co.uk/search/index.html?cx=018221729092257204127%3A2-4ig1wazeo&cof=FORID%3A10%3BNB%3A1&ie=UTF-8&q=Goad&siteurl=&sa.x=28&sa.y=6 Experian website: search results for "Goad"]</ref>
