{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=September 2018}} {{refimprove|date=August 2015}} {{Infobox museum | name = Indian Business Museum | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = | imagesize = | caption = Indian Business Museum | alt = | map_type = | map_caption = | map_alt = | map_size = | coordinates = | established = 2013 | dissolved = | location = [[Kozhikode]], [[Kerala]] | type = Specialized museum | collection = | visitors = | director = | president = | owner = [[Indian Institute of Management Kozhikode]] | curator = M.G. Sreekumar (convenor) | publictransit = | car_park = | network = | website = www.iimk.ac.in }}
The '''Indian Business Museum''' is located in the city of [[Kozhikode]], in the state of [[Kerala]], [[India]]. It was open in 2013<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/news/education/museum-of-indian-business-opened-at-iimkozhikode/article4541408.ece | title=Museum of Indian business opened at IIM-Kozhikode | date=23 March 2013 | newspaper=Hindu Business Line | accessdate=23 March 2013 | author=Bureau | location=Kozhikode}}</ref> and is dedicated to showcasing the rich traditions of Indian Business. The museum intends to collect, consolidate, and conserve the rich business [[history of India]]. The museum also seeks to inspire and ignite business entrepreneurship among the youth.
==Background== The museum was inaugurated in 2013 by then HRD Minister [[Palam Raju]]. The museum intends to inspire budding entrepreneurs by providing the rich trade history of Kozhikode and about business in India. Many business houses, including [[Tata Group|Tata]], [[Godrej Group|Godrej]], [[Reliance Anil Dhirubhai Ambani Group|Reliance]], [[Reserve Bank of India]] and [[Infosys]], have set up their pavilions inside the museum.<ref name=business>{{cite news|author = Hemali|title=First business museum of India opened |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/kozhikode/First-business-museum-of-India-opened/articleshow/19192460.cms|access-date=22 October 2016|newspaper=[[Times of India]]|date=25 March 2013|location=[[Mumbai]]}}</ref><ref name=museum>{{cite news|author = Abdul|title= Museum of Business History |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/education/college-and-university/museum-of-business-history/article2621783.ece/articleshow/19192460.cms|access-date=22 October 2016|newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|date=14 November 2011|location=[[Kozhikode]]}}</ref> The museum, spanning over {{convert|23,000|sqft}}, also has a [[Malabar Coast|Malabar]] Pavilion sponsored by the [[Malabar Chamber of Commerce]].
