{{BLP sources|date=May 2011}} '''Miguel Gellert Krigsner''' is a [[Bolivia]]n-[[Brazil]]ian [[entrepreneur]]. He is the president of the [[Brazil]]ian company [[O Boticário]],<ref name="Behrens2009">{{cite book|last=Behrens|first=Alfredo|title=Culture and management in the Americas|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oyR3RuAO8p0C&pg=PA338|accessdate=16 May 2011|date=2009-04-02|publisher=Stanford University Press|isbn=978-0-8047-6014-0|pages=338–}}</ref> the second major cosmetic company in the [[Southern Hemisphere]] (Natura is the first). Krigsner is also the founder of the Fundação de Proteção à Natureza, one of the main Brazilian environmental [[NGO]]s.
He was born in Bolivia into a [[Jews|Jewish]] family from [[La Paz]]. Born to Jacob Krigsner, a [[History of the Jews in Poland|Polish Jew]], and to Anneliese Krigsner, a [[History of the Jews in Germany|German Jew]]. The Krigsners left Bolivia and moved to Brazil when Miguel was 11 years old, settling in the city of [[Curitiba]].
